00:47:06.990 --> 00:47:08.500
that did 20, 30
years and help them

00:47:08.500 --> 00:47:11.870
get on that technological
kick or access to education.

00:47:11.870 --> 00:47:14.710
So if anything, I would just
say, look at our programs

00:47:14.710 --> 00:47:16.720
for bringing education
back in the system.

00:47:16.720 --> 00:47:19.606
JACOB SMITH: Any specific
example of organizations?

00:47:19.606 --> 00:47:22.000
AARON KINZEL: I know the
Vera Institute of Justice,

00:47:22.000 --> 00:47:25.250
which is a huge powerhouse
think tank of criminal justice.

00:47:25.250 --> 00:47:27.580
They threw a lot
of private dollars

00:47:27.580 --> 00:47:28.637
towards prison education.

00:47:28.637 --> 00:47:30.970
And they were one of the ones
that helped push that Pell

00:47:30.970 --> 00:47:32.620
Grant pilot that we
currently have here

00:47:32.620 --> 00:47:36.166
in the state of Michigan
and others across the US.

00:47:36.166 --> 00:47:38.700
MICHELLE SMART: So
our organization

00:47:38.700 --> 00:47:41.760
