home and that they have a job,

00:47:54.910 --> 00:47:57.450
they want to be able
to be self-sufficient.

00:47:57.450 --> 00:48:01.140
We are doing a lot of
collaborative things

00:48:01.140 --> 00:48:03.242
in the community
with organizations.

00:48:03.242 --> 00:48:04.950
There's another
organization, Rebel Nell,

00:48:04.950 --> 00:48:08.760
that does the graffiti
jewelry with women

00:48:08.760 --> 00:48:11.020
with barriers to employment.

00:48:11.020 --> 00:48:13.784
But as far as when
they come home

00:48:13.784 --> 00:48:16.200
and they know when they leave
those prison gates that they

00:48:16.200 --> 00:48:20.250
can come to our organization,
get an interview, and be hired,

00:48:20.250 --> 00:48:21.470
it's very-- it's crucial.

00:48:26.170 --> 00:48:32.570
KARLOS L. HARRIS: So DSDT,
we're kind of different.

00:48:32.570 --> 00:48:34.390
And so a lot of
the men and women

00:48:34.390 --> 00:48:37.690
that we train,
because of the lack

00:48:37.690 --> 00:48:41.080
of being able to bridge
them with employment,

00:48:41.080 --> 00:48:43.720
we've been creative
in hiring them.

00:48:43.720 --> 00:48:48.550
So at one time, I think we
were up near 30 individuals

00:48:48.550 --> 00:48:52.120
that we had employed
with us around March.

00:48:52.120 --> 00:48:54.230
And so that comes
through a lot of funding,

00:48:54.230 --> 00:48:59.080
whether it be through
the Department of Labor

00:48:59.080 --> 00:49:01.900
and some citywide
initiatives as well.

00:49:01.900 --> 00:49:07.270
So I think for us, when we're
showing up at these job fairs--

00:49:07.270 --> 00:49:11.680
and at times, we're truly
the only one employer

00:49:11.680 --> 00:49:17.020
of the returning citizens,
that says something to me.

00:49:17.020 --> 00:49:20.890
I've never heard of Bags to
Butterflies until literally I

00:49:20.890 --> 00:49:22.270
saw the flyer.

00:49:22.270 --> 00:49:23.770
And I don't know
if it's necessarily

00:49:23.770 --> 00:49:25.730
that we work in silos.

00:49:25.730 --> 00:49:29.320
It's just that the
information isn't out there.

00:49:29.320 --> 00:49:34.750
The only other organization
that I'm akin to is LUCK, Inc.

00:49:34.750 --> 00:49:36.250
And LUCK, Inc.
does a lot of work

00:49:36.250 --> 00:49:40.340
with returning citizens who've
been away for quite some time.

00:49:40.340 --> 00:49:45.850
And so I think that if
we are allowed somehow

00:49:45.850 --> 00:49:49.150
to come together and work more
as a team to kind of tackle

00:49:49.150 --> 00:49:51.760
what's facing our
community, it'll

00:49:51.760 --> 00:49:54.740
be more successful for
all of us in the long run.

00:49:54.740 --> 00:49:57.630
JACOB SMITH: And quick shout
